=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Reference_if_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring instant attack and sustained envelope, with evolving spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: evolving
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -6.4266
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7406
  pitch_clarity: 342.0983
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -7.5395
  resonance_freq: 430.6641

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: if Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Reference/if.html
// Tags: if, Reference
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
(
    {
        if( LFNoise1.kr(1.0,0.5,0.5) , SinOsc.ar, Saw.ar )
    }.play
)
